acne problems does anything work this is an answer not a question i've struggled with acne from age i expected it to go away when i reached adulthood but was i wrong it progressively got worse over the years and at i was at the end of my rope proactiv worked for a while and then didn't help me anymore not saying it might not work for others i found a new dr she diagnosed me with pcos and suggested a low dose tetracycline type antibiotic she said i would probably have to take it indefinitely it works i've been taking it for about months now i barely get blemishes anymore i may get or right before my cycle but that's it my face doesn't hurt anymore it feels soft to touch sometimes i still can't believe it i feel so much more confident now i can even leave home without foundation hope this helps if you have questions just ask best wishes d acne and pimples is one of the most distressing and depressing problem soak cotton wool in mint juice and apply every day mix cinnamon powder with lime juice to make a fine paste apply on pimples check out http sumiram googlepages com acne for more useful info Acne Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Isotretinoin Chronic fatigue syndrome Polycystic ovary syndrome God Emperor of Dune Textile manufacturing Puberty Avenue Q Keynesian economics Bipolar disorder Psoriasis Fecal incontinence Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Transsexuality Breastfeeding Stomach cancer Chocolate Pneumonia Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Babe Ruth Mattress Smallpox Kodocha Androgen insensitivity syndrome Hikikomori Vitamin C Controversies in autism Coffee Social rule Scar Tobacco smoking Tooth enamel One Tree Hill (TV series) Past teachings of Prem Rawat Clinical depression Prostate cancer Debugging Expert system Milton H. Erickson Wine Shaggy dog story Melanie Wilkes Tofu EastEnders Poker jargon Electrophysiology Milk Adult attention-deficit disorder Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Textile manufacturing terminology Domestic violence Cannabis (drug) Theory of cond